  "title": "EHS Executive (Chemical Plant) - West - WCDT",
  "description": "<p><em><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></em></p><ul><li>Assist in managing EHS administrative processes to ensure compliance with WSH regulations and legal requirements.</li><li>Support EHS systems in line with ISO 9001, ISO 45001, ISO 14001, and customer requirements, including participation in internal and external audits and follow-up on corrective actions.</li><li>Liaise with regulatory authorities, external auditors, and agencies on EHS-related matters.</li><li>Prepare documentation for approvals, licence applications and renewals, and other internal EHS records.</li><li>Support subcontractor safety management, including permit-to-work processes.</li><li>Assist in organising and conducting safety briefings, training, and emergency drills.</li><li>Provide administrative support for departmental tasks related to company maintenance activities.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><em><strong>Requirements:</strong></em></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Engineering, Environmental Science, or a related field, with at least 2 years of EHS experience.</li><li>Good knowledge of EHS requirements, including ISO 14001 and ISO 45001 standards.</li><li>WSH Coordinator certification or Advanced Certificate in Workplace Safety and Health is an advantage.</li><li>Familiar with risk assessment processes.</li><li>Good spoken and written English communication skills.</li><li>Basic proficiency in Microsoft Word, Excel, and PowerPoint.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Wecruit Pte Ltd | 20C0270<br />Tew Jie Wei | R22106822</p>",
